<div class="body" id="fhbody-175709983">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-175709983" class="p">
			
		 	
				Google has <a href="https://www.businessinsider.com/google-ceo-company-cut-manager-vp-roles-2024-12">reduced its senior management positions by 10%</a> as part of an ongoing efficiency initiative, CEO Sundar Pichai announced during a company-wide meeting earlier this week.<br> <br>

The restructuring affected managers, directors, and vice presidents, with some roles eliminated and others converted to non-management positions, a Google spokesperson told BusinessInsider. The move follows Google's January 2023 <a href="https://tech.slashdot.org/story/23/01/20/1240227/google-axes-12000-jobs">layoff of 12,000 employees</a> and Pichai's September 2022 goal to improve company efficiency by 20%.<br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
